Assignment 2 Part¶

Doing some extra cleaning to get data ready for analysis

As part of cleaning the duration_min will be converted to categorical data as we just want to understand how short or long songs affect the popularity

In [14]:
tracks['duration_cat'] = pd.qcut(tracks['duration_min'],q=10)
In [15]:
# Creating a column for the age of the song to use instead of release date.
# Picking 2021 to count from as the model will be used to predict 2021 data later
tracks['age'] = 2021 - pd.to_datetime(tracks['release_date']).dt.year

# converting release data to correct format and creating a release year column

# Creating a Multiple Linear Regression formula with non linear variables
formula = '''popularity ~ I(mode) + pow(instrumentalness,2) + +age + pow(age,2) + np.log(age) 
+ pow(instrumentalness,3) + np.log(instrumentalness+0.00000001) 
+ energy + pow(energy,2) + pow(energy,3) + np.log(energy+0.00000001) 
+ acousticness + pow(acousticness,2) + pow(acousticness,3) + np.log(acousticness+0.00000001) 
+ danceability + pow(danceability,2) + pow(danceability,3)
+ pow(speechiness,3) + np.log(speechiness+0.00000001) 
+ valence + pow(valence,2) + np.log(valence+0.00000001) 
+ liveness + pow(liveness,2) + pow(liveness,3) + np.log(liveness+0.00000001) 
+ duration_min  + pow(duration_min,2) + pow(duration_min,3) + np.log(duration_min) 
+ I(explicit) + loudness + tempo  + pow(tempo,3) 
+ np.log(tempo + 0.0000000001) + C(decade)''' 
model_test = smf.ols(formula, data=train,missing='drop')
